The paper proposes a sampling scheme for reducing a data set prior to selecting a hypothesis with minimum empirical risk, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of boosted trees suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.ST (Statistics).
